{"word":"G858 - ἀφελότης - aphelótēs - af-el-ot'-ace - Singleness","slug":"G858","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀφελότης</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>aphelótēs"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>af-el-ot'-ace"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Singleness"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03C6;&#x03B5;&#x03BB;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03C4;&#x03B7;&#x03C2; - aphelote&#x0304;s</b> - <i>af-el-ot'-ace</i><p/>From a compound of <a href=\"#/G1\">G1</a> (as a negative particle) and <b>&#x03C6;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03BB;&#x03BB;&#x03BF;&#x03C2;</b> <b>phellos</b> (in the sense of a <i>stone</i> as <i>stubbing</i> the foot); <i>smoothness</i>, that is, (figuratively) <i>simplicity:</i> - singleness."}]}